Package: BioTransition
Type: Package
Title: Detect Critical Transitions in Biological Systems
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Zaoqu", "Liu", 
        email = "liuzaoqu@163.com",
        role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Chuhan", "Zhang",
        role = "ctb",
        comment = "MDNB implementation"))
Maintainer: Zaoqu Liu <liuzaoqu@163.com>
Description: Identifies critical transition points and biomarker genes during 
    biological state transitions using Dynamic Network Biomarker (DNB) theory. 
    Implements seven state-of-the-art methods: conventional DNB (cDNB; Chen et al., 
    2012), topological DNB (tDNB), landscape DNB (LDNB; Liu et al., 2019), local 
    DNB (LcDNB), module-based DNB (MDNB; Li et al., 2022), time-series network 
    module biomarker (TSNMB; Zhong et al., 2022), and time-series leading edge 
    (TSLE; Liu et al., 2020). Optimized with C++ for computational efficiency. 
    Supports bulk RNA-seq, single-cell RNA-seq, and spatial transcriptomics data. 
    Includes curated human and mouse protein-protein interaction networks from 
    STRING database.
